A former street boy who was under the care of Jesus Lives Ministries Church was yesterday sentenced for stealing electronics worth Sh210,000 from the church.Amos Wafula pleaded guilty to breaking into the church and stealing the goods. He also damaged three flat screen TV sets.He stole cameras,microphones and a laptop on August 29.The court heard that Wafula who works for the church as a cook for their feeding program and also sleeps within the church stole the items from the church premises when he was left on that day.